data.description: This parcel is 3.13 acres. But, we have more land to offer - UPDATE ON THIS LISTING - WE HAVE NOW LISTED SEVERAL ADJACENT PARCELS FOR A TOTAL OF 30.03 COMBINED COMMERCIAL ACRES! Attention Commercial developers and investors. Here is your chance to own prime commercial real estate in the hot market of Auburndale, FL, JUST TWO MILES FROM THE BRAND NEW AMAZON DISTRIBUTION CENTER THAT IS NEAR THE END OF CONSTRUCTION AND ALREADY HIRING. Those 500+ employees will need affordable housing, gas stations, drug stores, retail, and somewhere to grab lunch. The land is currently used as residential, agriculture, pasture land, so this land is being offered for commercial purchase for the first time! Commercial uses: Permitted for Office Space, Research & Development. With Building Permit (C1), Gas station, Bar, Childcare Center, Light Assembly, Warehouse up to 50,000 sq ft C2 site review uses include, Banks, Restaurants, Hotel-Motels, Schools, Churches, Retail, Warehouse up to 250,000 sqft. This could be a great place for a strip mall with a couple of indoor-outdoor restaurants and shops. A place for all the biker and hiker foot traffic passing by every day on the Teco-Auburndale trail. This new shopping and restaurant area could really rival the area known as 92 and Berkley as the immediate area has no shopping or restaurants nearby and zero gas stations in the immediate area. The property owner for the adjacent acres to the north has also listed their property as commercial land. Nestled between Davenport and Lakeland, this 3.13 acre parcel includes a mobile home and is otherwise flat, clear, and ready for commercial development. Location is everything - This land is 2.1 miles from the new Amazon distribution site and this parcel is near the corner of Pace Road and Berkley Road, right by the Teco-Auburndale Trail. This parcel is minutes away from I-4, the Polk Parkway, and the new Lake Myrtle Sports Park. Auburndale is under 30 minutes from Disney, Universal, Lego Land, pretty much all the theme parks are within a 30 minute drive. Additional parcels include: 318 Sklyblue Lane, 307 and 317 Skyblue Lane, 314 Skyblue Lane, and 256 Sunridge Road (Sunridge becomes Skyblue, so different street name but same street). Only the land conveys on this sale, not the structures.
